<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Instructions - Quiz Maker</title>
    <style>
      * {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
        font-family: "Poppins", sans-serif;
      }

      body {
        background-color: #0b0119;
        color: aliceblue;
        display: flex;
        flex-direction: column;
        justify-content: center;
        align-items: center;
        height: 100vh;
        padding: 20px;
      }

      .instructions-container {
        width: 90%;
        max-width: 800px;
        text-align: center;
        padding: 20px;
        background: rgba(15, 2, 25, 0.95);
        border: 3px solid rgb(23, 161, 216);
        box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgb(23, 161, 216);
        border-radius: 10px;
      }

      h1 {
        color: rgb(23, 161, 216);
        text-shadow: 0 0 15px rgb(23, 161, 216);
        font-size: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }

      ul {
        text-align: left;
        margin: 20px 0;
        padding-left: 20px;
      }

      ul li {
        margin-bottom: 15px;
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        line-height: 1.5;
      }

      .btn-container {
        margin-top: 20px;
      }

      button {
        margin: 10px;
        padding: 10px 20px;
        background-color: rgb(23, 161, 216);
        color: black;
        font-weight: bold;
        border: none;
        border-radius: 8px;
        cursor: pointer;
        transition: 0.3s;
      }

      button:hover {
        box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgb(23, 161, 216);
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="instructions-container">
      <h1>Instructions</h1>
      <ul>
        <li>There are <strong>5 questions</strong> in this quiz.</li>
        <li>
          Each question has <strong>four options</strong>. Select the one you
          think is correct.
        </li>
        <li>You cannot change your answer once you select it.</li>
        <li>Your <strong>final score</strong> will be displayed at the end.</li>
        <li>Click on the "Start Quiz" button below to begin.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="btn-container">
        <button onclick="goToStartQuiz()">Start Quiz</button>
        <button onclick="goToHome()">Go Back to Home</button>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script>
      function goToStartQuiz() {
        window.location.href = "/startquiz"; // Redirect to the quiz page
      }

      function goToHome() {
        window.location.href = "/main"; // Redirect to the main.ejs page
      }
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
